                            {
                              "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
                              "Text": "# Soil Profile Description\r\n\r\nTempleton Silt Loam over sand, Typic Immature Pallic soil\r\n\r\n Horizon  Depth (cm) Description  \r\n Ah         0-28     Very dark grayish brown (10YR 3/2); silt loam; no stones; moderately developed fine to medium blocky structure  \r\n Bw(f)     28-55     Dark yellowish brown (10YR 4/4); silt loam; no stones; weakly developed coarse to very coarse blocky structure  \r\n Bw(g)     55-95     Olive brown (2.5Y 4/4); fine sandy loam; no stones; apedal massive  \r\n 2BC(g)    95-145    Olive brown (2.5Y 4/4); loamy sand;no stones; apedal single-grain  \r\n 3BCg     145-153    Light yellowish brown (2.5Y 6/3); silt loam; no stones; apedal massive\r\n 4BCg     153-200+   Light yellowish brown (2.5Y 6/3); medium sand; no stones; apedal single-grain\r\n ** 2BC(g) horizon contains a band of massive silt loam material between 115-130 cm  \r\n\r\nSampling layers:\r\nLayer  Depth (cm)  \r\n 1\t  0-15  \r\n 2\t 15-30  \r\n 3\t 30-60  \r\n 4\t 60-90  \r\n 5\t 90-120  \r\n 6\t120-150  \r\n 7\t150-180 -- Only for water  \r\n\r\nSoil parameterisation was based on the two description of the soil at the Rainshelter, with most data being a combination of \"templeton-2\" description (SWAMP survey) and the vbalues estimated based on the monitoring of the site.",
